description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a Band 5 Dietitian to work within the adult dietetic team at the Royal Victoria Infirmary. Working alongside a team of 29 dietitians across Newcastle Hospitals adult service, the successful applicant will assess, plan and implement care across a range of areas including General Medicine, Respiratory, Care of the Elderly, Urology and Gastroenterology in both the inpatient and outpatient settings. We offer ongoing training with the opportunity to experience dietetics in a wide range of different specialist areas. The Department also provides A, B and C placements for dietetic students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Dietetic Service enjoys a high profile with excellent multidisciplinary involvement. As part of the wider Dietetic Department, ‘Newcastle Nutrition’, you will also have support from colleagues at the RVI Hospital and Centre for Aging and Vitality sites. Our Dietetic teams are enthusiastic, committed and have established a first class reputation. Newcastle Hospitals are regarded as a centre of excellence and achieved “Outstanding” in the recent CQC inspection.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Deliver a high quality dietetic service to patients in the acute setting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Act as a source of expertise in nutrition support and dietetics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Deliver education and training to other hospital staff and to patient groups&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Participate in team and multi-disciplinary audit and research&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should be enthusiastic and self-motivated and will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Have a broad knowledge of general dietetics and evidence of continuous professional development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Be able to present and communicate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Have basic keyboard skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Be flexible, able to prioritize work and meet deadlines&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
